14/01/2009
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- A new round of talks aimed at resolving the long-standing name dispute between Macedonia and Greece will take place on February 11th in New York, UN mediator Matthew Nimetz announced late Monday (January 12th).
For the first time, Skopje's new representative in the talks, Zoran Jolevski, will take part in the meeting.
Diplomatic sources said Nimetz will offer a new package of ideas that will incorporate the latest comments by Athens and Skopje.
(A1, Deutsche Welle - 13/01/09)
